<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFD8FFD4FF21FDC5158EC138" blockId="15.[233,709,586,608]" box="[233,709,586,608]" pageId="15" pageNumber="712">
<heading id="D08281EBFFD8FFD4FF21FDC5158EC138" box="[233,709,586,608]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="15" pageNumber="712" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD8FFD4FF21FDC5158EC138" authority="(TOWNSEND, 1895)" baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[233,709,586,608]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="712" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fornax">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD8FFD4FF21FDC516A9C106" box="[233,482,587,608]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="712">COPESTYLUM FORNAX</emphasis>
(TOWNSEND, 1895)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFD8FFD4FF6CFDFC1671C0AE" blockId="15.[164,779,625,1014]" pageId="15" pageNumber="712">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD8FFD4FF6CFDFC15FCC1DE" box="[164,695,625,647]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="712">Puparium (lacking anterior prothoracic plate):</emphasis>
Dorsal abdominal vestiture confined to medial areas on the transverse bands. Ventral abdominal vestiture of varying length across folds: anterior sides of folds with longer setae than posterior sides. Posterior breathing tube red-brown, surface corrugated and shiny, about half width of puparium, and not tapering. TR barely discernable. AP bulging at apex and spiracular openings at apex with more curves than a simple s-shape. Pupal spiracles short, about 1.5¥ basal width, straight, shiny red with openings in upper third and separated by about 4.5¥ their length (
<figureCitation id="134E2A02FFD8FFD4FF64FC6E1664C0AE" box="[172,303,992,1014]" captionStart="Figures 48–53" captionStartId="47.[164,254,1555,1574]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1523]" captionTargetId="figure-0@47.[323,1283,195,1525]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="Figures 48–53. Pupal spiracles of Copestylum, scanning electron photomicrographs. 48, 50, Copestylum fornax; 48, dorsolateral view length 0.38 mm; 50, whole view from above scale as indicated; 49, Copestylum satur, lateral view length 0.73 mm; 51, 53, Copestylum marginatum; 51, dorsolateral view length 0.82 mm; 53, sculpture between openings, view from above; 52, Copestylum limbipenne, sculpture between openings, view from above." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443508/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="712">Figs 48, 50</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36F650CFFD8FFD4FF6CFBAF15D3C57C" pageId="15" pageNumber="712" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFD8FFD4FF6CFBAF1626C611" blockId="15.[164,779,1056,1353]" pageId="15" pageNumber="712">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD8FFD4FF6CFBAF1507C76D" box="[164,588,1056,1078]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="712">
Taxonomic notes: 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD8FFD4FEBCFBAE1507C76D" baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[372,588,1056,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="712" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fornax">Copestylum fornax</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD8FFD4FF00FBB11660C70C" baseAuthorityName="Osten Sacken" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[200,299,1087,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="712" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satur">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD8FFD4FF00FBB11660C70C" box="[200,299,1087,1108]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="712">C. satur</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD8FFD4FE6AFBB1152CC70C" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[418,615,1087,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="712" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraudulentum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD8FFD4FE6AFBB1152CC70C" box="[418,615,1087,1108]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="712">C. fraudulentum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD8FFD4FE89FBD3154BC72A" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[321,512,1117,1138]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="712" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraudulentum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD8FFD4FE89FBD3154BC72A" box="[321,512,1117,1138]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="712">C. fraudulentum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shallow TR and vestiture confined to medial areas of abdominal transverse folds. It is separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFD8FFD4FDF8FB1515DAC7E8" baseAuthorityName="Osten Sacken" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[560,657,1179,1200]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="712" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satur">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFD8FFD4FDF8FB1515DAC7E8" box="[560,657,1179,1200]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="712">C. satur</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a redbrown, nontapering AP which is the same length as a pupal spiracle, the shorter, 1.5¥ basal width pupal spiracles which are separated by more than 4¥ their length and by the more complex curves of the spiracular openings.
</paragraph>
